subSubSection.paragraph:
Posttemporal spine on the right side, short and pointed, the tip reaching to the base of 3rd spine of the first dorsal-fin; left posttemporal spine a little broken (the tip of posttemporal spine on left and right sides reaching to the base of 2nd spine of the first dorsal fin in 
paratype
). Two sharp preopercular spines present, the upper one longer than the lower. Opercular spine very long and stout, 123% of orbital diameter (144%), the tip extending posteriorly below the base of the 3rd spine of the first dorsal fin (reaching the 4th spine). No cleithral spine, posterior part of cleithrum a triangular plate.
